Package se.arkalix.net.http

Class HttpHeaders

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.arkalix.net.http.HttpHeaders
  • public class HttpHeaders
extends java.lang.Object
    A collection of HTTP header name/value pairs, where names are case-insensitive.

    When using this class, it is recommended to always use the lower-case form of header names. Lower-case is required when using HTTP/2.0 (see RFC 7540, Section 8.1.2), and sticking to lower-case means that less conversion overhead is introduced when such messages are sent.

    See Also:
    RFC 7230, Section 3.2, RFC 7231, Section 5, RFC 7231, Section 7, RFC 7540, Section 8.1.2, IANA Message Headers

      • add

        public HttpHeaders add​(java.lang.CharSequence name,
                       java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String> values)
        Adds headers, all with the given name, to this collection without replacing any existing pair with that name.

        The method may be though of as performing the equivalent of the following code: 

             for (final var value : values) {
         headers.add(name, value);
     }
        Parameters:
        name - Name of header. Not case sensitive. Prefer lowercase.
        values - New values to associate with header name.
        Returns:
        This collection.
        See Also:
        add(CharSequence, CharSequence)

        public HttpHeaders set​(java.lang.CharSequence name,
